BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Newcomer Settlement Services
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T140000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260306T220000Z
UID:698b8983491b809c6f18e882@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:New to Canada? Need information on employment\, housing\, lang
 uage learning\, schools\, or other topics? A Settlement Worker can help. D
 rop in to meet our settlement worker every Friday from 9 am-5 pm.\nVisit o
 ur branch or contact\nPranoti at 647-338-6300 or pmenon@ccscan.ca\nIn part
 nership with Catholic Cross-cultural Services.
LOCATION:Cedarbrae
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698b8983491b809c6f18e882
X-SOURCE:Volunteer Toronto
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Learn about Woodgreen Community Service
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T150000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T170000Z
UID:698b97f18d5e2d09335e55ea@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:For the month of March\, Woodgreen Community Services Staff wi
 ll be joining us every Thursday (11-1 PM) to help you connect with a var
 iety of services:\nNewcomer services\nEmployment services\nHousing\nFinanc
 ial empowerment\nYouth services\nSenior services\nBring a friend and learn
  about all the incredible resources and services available to you.\nThis e
 vent series is made possible through a collaboration between Fort York li
 brary and Woodgreen Community Services (King/Dufferin).
LOCATION:Fort York\, Ground Floor ATrium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698b97f18d5e2d09335e55ea
X-SOURCE:Volunteer Toronto
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Job interview Preparation – Mock Interview
